Package: cladesR
Type: Package
Title: Identify and Investigate Clades That Depart from Birth-Death Expectations
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Vincenzo A", "Ellis", email = "vaellis@udel.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Vincenzo A. Ellis <vaellis@udel.edu>
Description: Tools for comparing the sizes of same-aged clades to the geometric
    distribution expected under a homogeneous birth-death (speciation-extinction)
    process, flagging clades that contain more or fewer species than expected,
    and investigating how anomalous clades differ. The geometric progeny-size
    model and the conditional broken-stick null follow Nee, Mooers & Harvey
    (1992) <doi:10.1073/pnas.89.17.8322>; the clade-size diagnostics and the
    diversification-pulse framing follow Ricklefs (2003, 2005, 2014).
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    ape,
    phytools,
    stats
Suggests:
    clootl,
    ggplot2,
    lme4,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
